# renv dependency-discovery exclusions.
#
# inst/legacy_verification/ holds one-off verification scripts retained for
# provenance, not part of any routine pipeline:
#   - verify_jacobian.R  cross-checks the analytic Stage 2 Jacobian against
#                        numDeriv::jacobian on synthetic data (run once, passed)
#   - sandwich_se.R      legacy heteroskedastic SE reference
# These scripts self-document their own install requirements (e.g.
# verify_jacobian.R: install.packages(c("Rcpp", "numDeriv"))) and are run
# ad-hoc by a reader, not via renv::restore(). Excluding the directory keeps
# their ad-hoc dependencies (notably numDeriv, which is intentionally NOT in
# renv.lock) out of renv::status()/restore() so the production environment
# stays clean and the out-of-sync warning does not mask real issues.
inst/legacy_verification/